main event: A witness in Denver, Colorado observed three reddish-orange, slightly fluorescent objects in a definite triangular formation on October 6, 1967.
interesting points: The objects were round, about the size of a baseball, and made a definite humming sound after passing.
The objects moved rapidly at a speed greater than any jet aircraft, covering a southeasterly course in 8-12 seconds.
The witness happened to look up and see the objects due to their color and movement.
The objects were observed at an altitude of 2,000-3,000 feet.
The weather conditions were clear and calm at the time of the sighting.
sighted object: three glowing, reddish-orange objects in a triangular formation
witnesses: civilian witness, retired Navy lieutenant commander
